Util.!doc: L.Util contains various utility functions used throughout Leaflet code.

extend.!doc: shortcuts for most used utility functions

include.!doc: method for adding properties to prototype

mergeOptions.!doc: merge new default options to the Class

Class.!doc:
L.Class powers the OOP facilities of the library.
Thanks to John Resig and Dean Edwards for inspiration!

canvas.!doc: Vector rendering for all browsers that support canvas.

_add.!doc: destructive, used directly for performance in situations where it's safe to modify existing point

Point.!type: fn(x: number|[number], y: number, round: bool)
Point.!doc: L.Point represents a point with x and y coordinates.

extend.!doc: extend the bounds to contain the given point

Bounds.!doc: L.Bounds represents a rectangular area on the screen in pixel coordinates.

Transformation.!type: fn(a: number, b: number, c: number, d: number)
Transformation.!doc: L.Transformation is an utility class to perform simple point transformations through a 2d-matrix.

TRANSITION.!doc:
webkitTransition comes first because some browser versions that drop vendor prefix don't do
the same for the transitionend event, in particular the Android 4.1 stock browser

DomUtil.!doc: L.DomUtil contains various utility functions for working with DOM.

distanceTo.!doc: TODO move to projection code, LatLng shouldn't know about Earth

LatLng.!doc: L.LatLng represents a geographical point with latitude and longitude coordinates.

extend.!doc: extend the bounds to contain the given point or bounds

pad.!doc: extend the bounds by a percentage

LatLngBounds.!doc: L.LatLngBounds represents a rectangular area on the map in geographical coordinates.

SphericalMercator.!doc: Spherical Mercator is the most popular map projection, used by EPSG:3857 CRS used by default.

LonLat.!doc: Simple equirectangular (Plate Carree) projection, used by CRS like EPSG:4326 and Simple.

Mercator.!doc:
Mercator projection that takes into account that the Earth is not a perfect sphere.
Less popular than spherical mercator; used by projections like EPSG:3395.

Projection.!doc: L.Projection contains various geographical projections used by CRS classes.

Simple.!doc: A simple CRS that can be used for flat non-Earth maps like panoramas or game maps.

EPSG3857.!doc:
L.CRS.EPSG3857 (Spherical Mercator) is the most common CRS for web mapping
and is used by Leaflet by default.

EPSG4326.!doc: L.CRS.EPSG4326 is a CRS popular among advanced GIS specialists.

CRS.!doc: L.CRS is a base object for all defined CRS (Coordinate Reference Systems) in Leaflet.

setView.!doc: replaced by animation-powered implementation in Map.PanAnimation.js

getCenter.!doc: public methods for getting map state

getBoundsZoom.!type: fn(bounds: [[number, number], [number]], inside: bool, padding: [number]) -> number

getZoomScale.!doc: TODO replace with universal implementation after refactoring projections

_resetView.!doc: private methods that modify map state

_getMapPanePos.!doc: private methods for getting map state

_getCenterLayerPoint.!doc: layer point of the current center

_getCenterOffset.!doc: offset of the specified place to the current center in pixels

_limitCenter.!doc: adjust center for view to get inside bounds

_limitOffset.!doc: adjust offset for view to get inside bounds

_getBoundsOffset.!doc: returns offset needed for pxBounds to get inside maxBounds at a specified zoom

Map.!doc: L.Map is the central class of the API - it is used to create a map.

getTileUrl.!doc: image-specific code (override to implement e.g. Canvas or SVG tile layer)

_resetTile.!doc: Override if data stored on a tile needs to be cleaned up before reuse

TileLayer.!doc: L.TileLayer is used for standard xyz-numbered tile layers.

bringToFront.!doc: TODO remove bringToFront/bringToBack duplication from TileLayer/Path

ImageOverlay.!doc: L.ImageOverlay is used to overlay images over the map (to specific geographical bounds).

className.!doc:
iconUrl: (String) (required)
iconRetinaUrl: (String) (optional, used for retina devices if detected)
iconSize: (Point) (can be set through CSS)
iconAnchor: (Point) (centered by default, can be set in CSS with negative margins)
popupAnchor: (Point) (if not specified, popup opens in the anchor point)
shadowUrl: (String) (no shadow by default)
shadowRetinaUrl: (String) (optional, used for retina devices if detected)
shadowSize: (Point)
shadowAnchor: (Point)

Icon.!doc: L.Icon is an image-based icon class that you can use with L.Marker for custom markers.

_icon.!doc: TODO refactor into something shared with Map/Path/etc. to DRY it up

Marker.!doc: L.Marker is used to display clickable/draggable icons on the map.

LayerGroup.!doc:
L.LayerGroup is a class to combine several layers into one so that
you can manipulate the group (e.g. add/remove it) as one layer.

CLIP_PADDING.!doc:
how much to extend the clip area around the map view
(relative to its size, e.g. 0.5 is half the screen in each direction)
set it so that SVG element doesn't exceed 1280px (vectors flicker on dragend if it is)

SVG_NS.!doc: Extends L.Path with SVG-specific rendering code.

Path.!doc: L.Path is a base class for rendering vector paths on a map. Inherited by Polyline, Circle, etc.

simplify.!doc:
Simplify polyline with vertex reduction and Douglas-Peucker simplification.
Improves rendering performance dramatically by lessening the number of points to draw.

pointToSegmentDistance.!doc: distance from a point to a segment between two points

_simplifyDPStep.!type: fn(points: [+L.Point], markers: [number], sqTolerance: number, first: number, last: number)

_reducePoints.!doc: reduce points that are too close to each other to a single point

clipSegment.!doc:
Cohen-Sutherland line clipping algorithm.
Used to avoid rendering parts of a polyline that are not currently visible.

_lastCode.!doc: save 2nd code to avoid calculating it on the next segment

_sqDist.!doc: square distance (to avoid unnecessary Math.sqrt calls)

_sqClosestPointOnSegment.!type: fn(p: +L.Point, p1: +L.Point, p2: +L.Point, sqDist: bool) -> number
_sqClosestPointOnSegment.!doc: return closest point on segment or distance to that point

clipPolygon.!doc:
Sutherland-Hodgeman polygon clipping algorithm.
Used to avoid rendering parts of a polygon that are not currently visible.

addListener.!type: fn(obj: ?, type: string, fn: fn(e: +Event) -> L.DomEvent|fn(), context: +L.Popup|?) -> !this
addListener.!doc: inspired by John Resig, Dean Edwards and YUI addEvent implementations

<i>.!doc: reset when checking, as it's only used in map container and propagates outside of the map

_checkMouse.!doc: check if element really left/entered the event target (for mouseenter/mouseleave)

_filterClick.!doc: this is a horrible workaround for a bug in Android where a single touch triggers two click events

addDoubleTapListener.!doc: inspired by Zepto touch code by Thomas Fuchs

addPointerListener.!type: fn(obj: ?, type: string, handler: fn(e: +Event) -> ?, id: number) -> L.DomEvent.addPointerListenerStart.!ret|L.DomEvent

addPointerListenerStart.!type: fn(obj: ?, type: string, handler: fn(e: +Event) -> ?, id: number) -> !this

addPointerListenerMove.!type: fn(obj: ?, type: string, handler: fn(e: +Event) -> ?, id: number) -> !this

addPointerListenerEnd.!type: fn(obj: ?, type: string, handler: fn(e: +Event) -> ?, id: number) -> !this

DomEvent.!doc: L.DomEvent contains functions for working with DOM events.

Draggable.!doc: L.Draggable allows you to add dragging capabilities to any element. Supports mobile devices too.

Handler.!doc:
L.Handler is a base class for handler classes that are used internally to inject
interaction features like dragging to classes like Map and Marker.

Control.!doc:
L.Control is a base class for implementing map controls. Handles positioning.
All other controls extend from this class.

callInitHooks.!doc: add method for calling all hooks

_stepTimer.!doc: there's no native way to track value updates of transitioned properties, so we imitate this

_transformRe.!doc:
you can't easily get intermediate values of properties animated with CSS3 Transitions,
we need to parse computed style (in case of transform it returns matrix string)

PosAnimation.!doc:
L.PosAnimation fallback implementation that powers Leaflet pan animations
in browsers that don't support CSS3 Transitions.
